news.title: Punjab to develop new urban estates in smaller towns
news.para: Arora also asked the officials to hold meetings with Resident Welfare Associations (RWAs) to conduct development works so that the residents don't face any hardship.

news.title: Ambuja Cements declared as preferred bidder for Uskalvagu limestone block in Odisha
news.para: Uskalvagu limestone block is situated in Malkangiri district over an area of ~547 hectare with estimated limestone resource of ~141 million tonnes having average calcium oxide (CaO) content of 43.74 per cent.

news.title: Circle rate of land increased in Uttarakhand
news.para: While the circle rates are revised annually, the process was held for the past two years due to Covid-19. In 2023, the rates were revised for 57,000 areas across Uttarakhand. Across the total identified areas, the circle rate was increased by less than 50% in the majority of the areas.

news.title: Embassy REIT raises debt of Rs 1,000 crore from Bajaj Housing Finance
news.para: Embassy Office Parks REIT (Embassy REIT) will use the proceeds of this debt raise primarily to repay existing construction debt and for general corporate purposes.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: VMRDA identifies 162 vacant plots, to sell them in phases
news.para: The urban development authority has so far conducted two rounds of auctions for a total 78 of these 162 vacant plots. The sale of 31 plots (out of the 78 that have been put to auction) fetched about Rs 35 crore to the VMRDA.

news.title: Zirakpur & Kharar may face serious damage due to haphazard constructions
news.para: Recently, many under constriction buildings had collapsed, without any earthquake, in Zirakpur and Kharar, proving that there was some lapse in the construction and designing plan which brought down the building.

news.title: Unique identity numbers for New Town addresses in Kolkata
news.para: The authorities will receive residents' feedback and suggestions over the next 14 days. The proposal, once finalised and introduced, would be the first of its kind for any civic body area in the state.

news.title: Haryana power generation corporation sells fly ash, upsets brick kiln owners, cement manufacturers
news.para: The HPGCL has initiated the process to sell of the fly off through auction, triggering major unrest among the brick kiln owners as well as those supplying fly ash to various companies manufacturing cement as well as laying roads.

news.title: Patna civic body targets Rs 120 crore tax collection by March 3
news.para: Under the special campaign, called 'Mission Rs 120 crore revenue', the civic body aims to collect Rs 120 crore through property and service taxes by March 3.

news.title: Jamshedpur notified area committee cracks down on illegal buildings
news.para: Notices had been served to the owners of these buildings for flouting the Jharkhand Building Bye Laws and Municipal Act rules, he added.

news.title: No conversion of commercial properties to freehold: Chandigarh administration
news.para: In a letter to the CHB, the administration has said there is no policy under which conversion can be allowed for the CHB’s commercial properties. The CHB has been pursuing the permission for more than a year.

news.title: West Bengal Budget 2023: Govt extends rebate on stamp duty, circle rates till Sept 2023
news.para: Chandrima Bhattacharya informed that the West Bengal real estate regulatory authority (West Bengal RERA) and West Bengal real estate administrative tribunal (West Bengal REAT) have been established.

news.title: Builders in Punjab hail 'move' to waive off late payment charges on NOCs
news.para: Businessmen claimed that they have received a confirmation in this regard from senior officials of the state government. A formal notification is expected soon.

news.title: Over 70 demolition drives carried out in south Delhi this year so far: MCD
news.para: In a statement, the MCD's South Zone said it has conducted a demolition and sealing drive against "unauthorized constructions" in different areas of South Delhi.

news.title: SBI hikes MCLR-based lending rates by 10 bps to 7.95-8.70%
news.para: According to the SBI website, the bank has increased the overnight lending rate, based on the marginal cost of funds-based lending rate, by 10 bps to 7.95 per cent, while the same for one-and three-month maturity has been increased to 8.10 per cent.
